fman_pcd: FE-VM arm - real AC_CC encoding (Phase 1 D9-B, board 0133)

Board patch 0132 shipped the fe_arm 'engage' verb but armed the KeyGen
scheme with the KGSE_CCBS placebo (next_engine=2, mode 0x80500002): per
the CC-dispatch truth table that encoding NEVER invokes the CC walk -
frames bypass into plain RSS, so an arm through it is a false positive.

This corrects the arm to the REAL AC_CC encoding: a new next_engine==3
branch in keygen_scheme_setup emits KGSE_MODE = FM_CTL|AC_CC (0x80000006)
with KGSE_CCBS=0, and fman_pcd_kg_port_arm_fe() sets next_engine=3 /
cc_bits_sel=0.  The FMBM_RCCB write (-> FE_ENTER root AD) is unchanged and
already correct.  The two NIA_ENG_FM_CTL / NIA_FM_CTL_AC_CC defines that
0118 dropped are re-added (used only by the new branch; the CCBS
implicit-walk graft for next_engine==2 is untouched, as are the policer,
M1-engage and RSS paths).  disarm is unchanged (forces next_engine=0).

Ships DORMANT: the encoding only takes effect on an explicit echo to the
fman_pcd/<id>/fe_arm debugfs node.  This is the make-or-break M2 dispatch
experiment - the only encoding that genuinely enters the FE VM terminal
disposition that a bare exact-match leaf lacks (M3-3b iter-50 park).

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
@@ -124,5 +124,15 @@
  * only ORs in CCOBASE.
  */
 #define KG_SCH_MODE_CCOBASE_SHIFT	24
+
+/* Next-engine = real Coarse-Classification AC_CC dispatch (board 0133,
+ * Fork-B FE-VM arm).  Re-added after 0118 dropped them: with these the
+ * KGSE_MODE NIA flips to FM_CTL|AC_CC (0x80000006) so the FMan
+ * controller walks the CC root named by the port's FMBM_RCCB.  Used
+ * only by next_engine==3 (the FE_ENTER arm); the CCBS implicit-walk
+ * graft (next_engine==2) is untouched.
+ */
+#define NIA_ENG_FM_CTL			0x00000000
+#define NIA_FM_CTL_AC_CC		0x00000006
 
 /* Hard-coded configuration:
@@ -564,6 +564,17 @@ int keygen_scheme_setup(struct fman_keygen *keygen, u8 scheme_id,
 			tmp_reg |= ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA |
 				(scheme->cc_base_offset <<
 				 KG_SCH_MODE_CCOBASE_SHIFT);
+		} else if (scheme->next_engine == 3) {
+			/* Next engine = real Coarse Classification AC_CC
+			 * (board 0133, Fork-B FE-VM arm): NIA = FM_CTL |
+			 * AC_CC (mode 0x80000006) so the FMan controller
+			 * walks the CC root named by the port's FMBM_RCCB -
+			 * here the FE_ENTER root AD.  KGSE_CCBS stays 0.
+			 * A bare exact-match leaf parks with no disposition
+			 * (M3-3b iter-50); the FE VM behind FMBM_RCCB
+			 * supplies the terminal BMI-FIFO disposition.
+			 */
+			tmp_reg |= NIA_ENG_FM_CTL | NIA_FM_CTL_AC_CC;
 		} else {
 			/* Enqueue frame NIA */
 			tmp_reg |= ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA;
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
@@ -2105,8 +2105,8 @@ static const struct file_operations fman_pcd_fe_hashfe_fops = {
 
 /*
  * fe_arm - arm the FE-VM datapath on a single FMan RX port (Phase 1
- * D9-B, patch 0132).  Reprograms the port's KGSE scheme to next_engine=CC
- * with KGSE_CCBS = FE_ENTER root-AD offset and sets the BMI fmbm_rccb, via
- * the KeyGen helpers in fman_pcd_kg.c (HW-proven KGSE_CCBS approach, 0118).
+ * D9-B, patch 0132; arm encoding corrected by board 0133).  Reprograms the
+ * port's KGSE scheme to the REAL AC_CC NIA (next_engine=3, mode 0x80000006)
+ * and points the BMI fmbm_rccb at the FE_ENTER root AD.
  * eth3 / hw port 0x10 only in practice.  The node lives here (not in a
  * separate TU) so it can read pcd->fe_refcount / pcd->fe_root_ad_off
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c
@@ -729,16 +729,19 @@ int fman_pcd_kg_port_arm_fe(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 hw_port_id,
 	}
 	*saved_engine = slot->next_engine;
 
-	/*
-	 * Arm the FE datapath (Fork B, Phase 1 D9-B).
-	 * Use the KGSE_CCBS approach (HW-proven per 0118): set kgse_ccbs
-	 * to the FE_ENTER AD offset; the CC walk fires because ccbs is
-	 * non-zero; NIA stays BMI direct-enqueue.  The CC engine resolves
-	 * its root from the BMI port's fmbm_rccb (set in step 2).
-	 */
-	slot->next_engine    = 2;
-	slot->cc_base_offset = 0;
-	slot->cc_bits_sel    = fe_enter_off;
+	/*
+	 * Arm the FE datapath (Fork B, Phase 1 D9-B; arm encoding
+	 * corrected by board 0133).  Use the REAL AC_CC NIA, the only
+	 * encoding that actually dispatches the CC walk: next_engine=3
+	 * makes keygen_scheme_setup emit KGSE_MODE = FM_CTL|AC_CC
+	 * (0x80000006) with KGSE_CCBS=0.  The CC root is the FE_ENTER
+	 * AD, named at the BMI port's fmbm_rccb (set in step 2); the
+	 * FE VM behind it supplies the terminal BMI-FIFO disposition
+	 * a bare exact-match leaf lacks (M3-3b iter-50 park).
+	 */
+	slot->next_engine    = 3;
+	slot->cc_base_offset = 0;
+	slot->cc_bits_sel    = 0;
 	slot->used = false;
 	err = keygen_scheme_setup(keygen, id, true);
 	if (err) {
@@ -767,8 +767,8 @@ int fman_pcd_kg_port_arm_fe(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 hw_port_id,
 		return err;
 	}
 
-	pr_info("fman_pcd: port 0x%02x FE-ARMED (fmbm_rccb=0x%x, kgse_ccbs=0x%x)\n",
-		hw_port_id, fe_enter_off, fe_enter_off);
+	pr_info("fman_pcd: port 0x%02x FE-ARMED (kgse_mode=AC_CC fmbm_rccb=0x%x kgse_ccbs=0)\n",
+		hw_port_id, fe_enter_off);
 	return 0;
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(fman_pcd_kg_port_arm_fe);
diff --git a/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h b/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h
--- a/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h
+++ b/include/linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h
@@ -286,8 +286,8 @@ int fman_pcd_kg_port_attach_cc(struct fman_pcd *pcd, u8 hw_port_id,
  *                engaged pcd->fe_root_ad_off)
  * @saved_engine: out - the scheme's prior next_engine, for restore
  *
- * Reprograms the port's KGSE scheme to next_engine=CC with
- * KGSE_CCBS = @fe_enter_off and sets the BMI fmbm_rccb (HW-proven
- * KGSE_CCBS approach, patch 0118).  NIA stays BMI direct-enqueue.
+ * Reprograms the port's KGSE scheme to the real AC_CC NIA (next_engine=3,
+ * mode 0x80000006, KGSE_CCBS=0) and points the BMI fmbm_rccb at
+ * @fe_enter_off (the FE_ENTER root AD).  Corrected from the 0132 CCBS form.
  *
  * Return: 0 on success; negative errno (scheme/port restored on failure).
